cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Project Zero in academic work, please cite it as below."
title: "Project Zero — CPU LLM Inference Engine"
abstract: >-
  A from-scratch, single-binary LLM inference engine written in C, built to run
  Microsoft's BitNet b1.58-2B-4T ternary weights at maximum speed on commodity
  CPUs. Also runs DeepSeek-V2-Lite-Chat (MoE + MLA) from GGUF, with SIMD-dispatched
  kernels (AVX-512/AVX2/NEON), an mmap weight loader, a vision pipeline, agentic
  tools, and RAG persistent memory. No GPU and no ML framework.
type: software
authors:
  - alias: shifulegend
    name: "Project Zero Contributors"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/shifulegend/project-zero"
keywords:
  - llm
  - inference
  - cpu
  - bitnet
  - ternary
  - quantization
  - simd
  - mixture-of-experts
  - gguf
